<big><big><big><big><center><span style="font-family: Special Elite>Innocent Ball Pit</span></center></big></big></big></big>



<center><big>T</big>hat was the ''year'' colossal girders rose abruptly at the city’s edge,</center>
<br>
<center>while heavy cranes tore open the dusk, erecting the skeleton of desire.</center>
<br>
<center>On the day of the ribbon-cutting, the scarlet sash was severed beneath a storm of flashing cameras—</center>
<br>
<center>and the falling ribbon looked like a cursed blaze of ambition,</center>
<br>
<center>igniting at once the dry timber of greed in the eyes of men dressed in polished suits.</center>
<br>
<center>“For the laughter of <span style="background:linear-gradient(to right, yellow, yellow); text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em white, 0em 0em 1.0em white; -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent">CHILDREN</span>. For the dreams of <span style="font-family: Cinzel>tomorrow</span>.”</center>
<br>
<center>So proclaimed the <span style="font-family: uberh><big><big>newspaper</big></big></span> headlines, solemn and magnificent,</center>
<br>
<center>as though this place were an ark bound for heaven, rather than a trap built for profit.</center>
<br>
<center>The parent company loomed like a colossal idol sculpted from money and power,</center>
<br>
<center>gazing down upon the masses from its cold kingdom in the clouds.</center>
<br>
<center>Then, like an octopus, it unfurled countless mucus-slick tentacles,</center>
<br>
<center>reaching, probing, fastening themselves to every corner they could touch.</center>
<br>
<center>And one of the smallest, most insignificant among them settled into the noisy corner of a shopping mall—</center>
<br>
<center>an indoor playground for children,</center>
<br>
<center>advertised as a kingdom of joy, <span style="font-family: fabulous script>d</span><span style="font-family: christmaseve>r</span><span style="font-family: river stone personal use><small><small>e</small></small></span><span style="font-family: mynerve>a</span><span style="font-family: spinach outline>m</span><span style="font-family: playfair display sc><small>s</small></span>, and absolute safety.</center>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-size: 2.5em; float: left; line-height: 0.85em; margin-top: 0.1em; margin-right: 0.1em; font-family: Times New Roman;">M</span>ore than a decade later, bloated branches had grown from it.
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: extravaganza-><big><big><big><big><big>S</big></big></big></big></big></span>till colorful—though now merely another subsidiary branch store—
<br>
<br>

wedged into the clamorous corner of a department store,
<br>
<br>

selling polished sugarcoating and the shrill screams of children at play.
<br>
<br>

Beside the sea of bright plastic balls,
<br>
<br>

a figure stood numbly clutching a rag.
<br>
<br>

Paid the thinnest hourly wage,
<br>
<br>

living the lowest, most wretched kind of life.
<br>
<br>

Their uniform had yellowed with time; their eyes were hollow.
<br>
<br>

Every day, amid endless shrieks and laughter,
<br>
<br>

the burden of existence pressed so hard upon them they could scarcely breathe.
<br>
<br>






<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>This place sold beautiful illusions,</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>yet beneath its cheerful wrapping it was a spiritual slaughterhouse,</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>slicing human energy apart piece by piece</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>and stuffing it into cheap plush toys.</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>Somewhere above, men seated comfortably in clouds counted their money,</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>while the screws at the bottom slowly corroded beneath noise and disinfectant fumes.</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>Freedom here was worthless—</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>nothing more than cold digits flickering on a timer,</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>replaceable at any moment by someone younger, cheaper, more disposable.</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>Sometimes, watching those children laugh carefree within the ball pit,</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>a vile jealousy would rise within—</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>why were their tomorrows meant for dreams,</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>while self was only another endless night of sweeping trash and fragments after closing time?</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>Life had wrung this one dry,</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>leaving only a numb shell to rot day after day beneath cheerful background music.</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>And the pathetic creature crushed breathless in the corner by the weight of living—</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>you ask who that is?</span>
<br>
<br>

<span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville>Heh.</span>
<br>
<br>

'''ꓕɥɐʇ ʍonןp qǝ ɯǝ˙'''


<div style="font-family: Island Moments"><div style="text-align: right;"><big><big><big>Oh, within that gaudy, filth-concealing ocean of plastic balls,</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="font-family: Island Moments"><div style="text-align: right;"><big><big><big>among tunnels and slides stinking faintly of synthetic chemicals,</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>I spent my days grinding away the years of my cheaply sold youth.</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>I would stare at my payslip, thin as a cicada’s wing,</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>the numbers upon it too pitiful even to buy a single child’s outfit from the mall.</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>My life was a ruined wall,</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>its foundations long since rotted through.</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right; white-space: nowrap;"><div style="font-family: 'romantic party'; display: inline;">Nothing </div><div style="font-family: 'Island Moments'; display: inline;"><big><big><big>was good.</big></big></big> </div><div style="font-family: 'romantic party'; display: inline;">Nothing.</div></div>


<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: alexturners"><big><big><big>Every day I had to wear a counterfeit smile,</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: alexturners"><big><big><big>pretending friendliness without end for customers I could no longer care about.</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>In my ears the same melodies repeated forever,</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>and my irritation echoed in endless loops with them.</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>Somewhere in the dark unseen machinery of existence,</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>beneath the strain of meaningless labor,</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>my heart continued to pulse—</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>faintly, chaotically, hopelessly.</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>I wanted to escape.</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>A thousand times I wanted to tear off that suffocating uniform.</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>I wanted to scream against the endless injustice of those hours,</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>against wages so humiliatingly unequal to sweat and exhaustion.</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>Each night I returned home and looked into the cracked mirror,</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>at the bloodshot eyes staring back at me,</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>and I wanted to spit directly into the face of the world that consumed people whole.</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: akaya">Why?</div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: akaya">Why did their fortunes double in the stock market,</div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: akaya">while after an entire day of labor my dinner could only be buckwheat bread?</div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>This miserable job—this cursed place—</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>clung to me like an enormous leech latched onto flesh,</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>draining my youth, draining my blood,</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="font-family: Island Moments"><big><big><big>while still demanding that every week I insist I felt fine. Fine.</big></big></big></div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">Then came the day the gears of fate jammed into place.</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">It was my turn to supervise the shift.</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">The air smelled of burnt-sweet popcorn and faintly acrid disinfectant.</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">Late in the afternoon, as the sun leaned westward, he wandered in slowly.</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">A child.</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">His eyes avoided everyone around him.</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">A heavy schoolbag hung from his shoulders,</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">though it was an hour no child should have been free.</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">Obviously, unmistakably, he was skipping school—</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">a runaway with nowhere else to go.</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">I should have approached him.</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">I should have followed protocol, asked questions, written a report.</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">But I was too exhausted.</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">Too many overtime shifts had hollowed out every remaining trace of righteousness inside me.</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">The numbness born of low wages and endless fatigue had hardened into a thick cocoon,</div></div>



<div style="font-family:IM Fell English SC"><div style="margin-left: 20%;">and so I turned away, pretending I saw nothing at all.</div></div>



<div style="margin-left: 55%;"><big><span style="font-family: 'The Poison';">Th<span style="font-family: 'Apple Tree'; display: inline-block; vertical-align: baseline;">a</span>t <span style="font-family: 'Apple Tree'; display: inline-block; vertical-align: baseline;">i</span>s h<span style="font-family: 'Apple Tree'; display: inline-block; vertical-align: baseline;">o</span>w tr<span style="font-family: 'Apple Tree'; display: inline-block; vertical-align: baseline;">a</span><span style="font-family: 'Apple Tree'; display: inline-block; vertical-align: baseline;">g</span><span style="font-family: 'Apple Tree'; display: inline-block; vertical-align: baseline;">e</span><span style="font-family: 'Apple Tree'; display: inline-block; vertical-align: baseline;">d</span>y <span style="font-family: 'Apple Tree'; display: inline-block; vertical-align: baseline;">b</span>r<span style="font-family: 'Apple Tree'; display: inline-block; vertical-align: baseline;">ee</span><span style="font-family: 'Apple Tree'; display: inline-block; vertical-align: baseline;">d</span>s—</span></big></div>



